The paper discusses convergence of a class of adaptive gradient algorithms commonly used in deep learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also provides convergence analysis for nonconvex optimization, which is a common problem in numerical analysis (cs.NA). The use of stochastic optimization and analysis of convergence rates suggests a connection to the field of data science (cs.DS). The algorithms discussed in the paper are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification and object detection (cs.CV). Finally, the paper's focus on optimization and convergence analysis suggests a connection to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
